Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, suggesting possible renal impairment. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, bilirubinuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine color and odor, but no hematuria, nitrites, or leukocytes. These findings may indicate renal dysfunction (possibly tubular), with no clear evidence of infection. Further nephrological evaluation is recommended.
